DataElement.preferredName: Imaging Technique Observation Reuse Template Study Activity Repeat Quantity ISO21090.URG.INT.NONNEG.v1.0
DataElement.preferredDefinition: An activity defined at the global library level whose intention is to obtain pictures of the interior or exterior of the body usually for diagnostic reasons. EXAMPLE(S): X-ray, MRI The number of times the activity occurs. NOTE(S): If the frequency is more than once a day, this is still interpreted per time, e.g. BID for 5 days = 10 repeats.
